    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-04T00:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-04T00:40:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1077.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-04T01:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1914, 1 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Provisional Government in direful dilemma. Arias sends Bordas final demand for
                    Vice President and three hundred thousand dollars. Provisional Government knows
                    he is preparing for revolution. Provisional Government will decide at eleven
                    this morning whether to precipitate the inevitable or meet him in Puerto Plata.
                    Bordas will absolutely refuse both money and office. Banks will not loan on your
                    proposition. With funds Government can maintain law and order; without funds
                    chaos will reign. Jimenezistas seize opportunity to start anti-American campaign
                    calling Bordas the pro-American candidate. I recommend instant substantial
                    support of Provisional Government.</p>
                <p>Provisional Government asks for sale of half million bonds immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
